reviews.review: I thought the movie was amazing, totally worthy of ending the trilogy

This was a GREAT GREAT GREAT movie! Finally a Disney Star Wars film that has emotion. Don't listen to all the critics of this movie. Go see it for yourself and decide. It is the best movie from this crappy trilogy. It is the best of the three. Very fun movie. JJ actually knows how to make a good Star Wars movie unlike another, not to be mentioned director. Go see it!
So glad this film got back to what made us love Star Wars in the first place.

nothing really new new, but like catching up with good old friends...good movie.
it is however though in retrospect a typical Disney feel good happy end movie.

In what is the frustrated final film, intended close out the 9-part Skywalker saga, the convoluted video game-like plot consists of a breakneck search for a series of MacGuffins in which convenient things happen and characters occur because … plot. Which clearly reveals the filmmakers went into this trilogy without a plan.

JJ Abrams attempts to salvage what he can from the previous film - The Last Jedi - that subverted Disney's sequel trilogy and derailed any intended story arc, but there's little left to work with. So what he concocts is a cobbled-together narrative mess flying all over the place, throwing in plenty of nostalgia points in an attempt to win back the old fans it has alienated. But what he serves up are hollow characters, a hollow story, and hollow emotions – with the Emperor Palapatine retconned back from the dead since the main villain (Snoke) was prematurely killed in the last film. And even the set-pieces are a let down.

True to the original formula!  Highly entertaining and loved it!
Critics hate everything but real fans enjoy the ride!
Epic ending! Great way to finish out the story. Don't listen to the critics!
It was pretty good!  Haters gonna hate

The movie stayed true to the franchise, and finished the sky walker saga with a bang! Must see if you are a Star Wars fan, and regardless of the current score, is a great movie. The twists are pretty typical of this franchise. I had no issues with this film and will be watching it again.
